#Text=Pennsburg
#Text=Pennsburg is a city in Montgomery County in Pennsylvania
#Text=Understand
#Text=Pennsburg , Pennsylvania is a small town in Montgomery County that prides itself on being a family oriented , welcoming community .
#Text=It is part of the Upper Perkiomen School District .
#Text=Get in
#Text=From Pottstown : Route 663 East
#Text=From Philadelphia : Route 476 North to PA Turnpike North .
#Text=PA Turnpike to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=From New York and Northern Jersey : George Washington Bridge to I80 West to Route 33 South .
#Text=Route 22 West to PA Turnpike .
#Text=South on PA Turnpike to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=OR I78 West to Route 33 North .
#Text=Route 22 West to PA Turnpike ( Route 476 ) .
#Text=South on PA Turnpike to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West to Geryville Pike ( 2nd light past Turnpike ) .
#Text=From Reading : Route 222 North to Route 309 South to Route 663 West .
#Text=From Allentown : Route 309 South to Route 663 West .
#Text=Follow Route 663 past PA Turnpike .
#Text=From Lancaster : Route 222 North to Route 309 South to Route 663 West .
#Text=Follow Route 663 past PA Turnpike .
#Text=From the Poconos : I-80 West to Route 33 South .
#Text=Route 22 West to PA Turnpike .
#Text=South on PA Turnpike to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=From Wilkes-Barre : PA Turnpike ( Route 476 South ) to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=From Stroudsburg : Route 33 South to Route 22 West to PA Turnpike ( Route 476 ) .
#Text=South on PA Turnpike to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=From Bloomsburg : I80 East to Route 33 South .
#Text=Route 22 West to PA Turnpike ( Route 476 ) .
#Text=South on PA Turnpike to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=From Maryland ( Baltimore ) : I95 North to Route 476 North .
#Text=PA Turnpike North to Quakertown / Pottstown Exit #44 .
#Text=Right on Route 663 West .
#Text=See
#Text=Unami Creek .
#Text=The beautiful Unami Creek is home to a variety wildlife and spectacular scenery .
#Text=The area hosts white tailed deer , turkeys , woodpeckers , different varieties of hawks , and great blue herons , among others .
#Text=Schwenkfelder Library and Heritage Center .
#Text=Here you can find the history of the Upper Perkiomen Valley region .
#Text=Perkiomen Prep School .
#Text=A private boarding and day school .
#Text=Notable alumni include Al Dublin , John Cecil Holm , and Harold Schaffer .
#Text=Do
#Text=Perkiomen Trail .
#Text=A 19 mile long trail lining the Perkiomen Creek that offers horse trails , jogging , biking , or just sight-seeing .
#Text=Green Lane Park .
#Text=Boasts fishing , boating , camping , tennis , and ice skating as well as a playground and plenty of picnicking space !
#Text=Pennsburg Nature Preserve .
#Text=Peaceful and serene walking trails located right off of East 5th Street .
#Text=The Grand Theater , 252 Main Street East , Greenville .
#Text=An affordable , family oriented movie theater that features a large stage , 12,000 watts sound system , and even a VIP section .
#Text=Once called the Old Valley Theater , it was renovated in 2004 and is now celebrating its 86th anniversary .
#Text=Macoby Run Golf Course , 5275 McLean Station Rd , Green Lane .
#Text=The front 9 holes have a 138 ' of elevation change with both hills and trees to keep you on point .
#Text=The back 9 holes offer a bit of a reprieve with open terrain .
#Text=Sweet Water Golf Course , 2554 Geryville Pike .
#Text=A " 2777 yard par 36 with even two par 5 ’s – one of them the 475-yard No. 4 .
